===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# {{senseid|en|Q8187550}} {{lb|en|medicine|pathology}} Deficiency or absence of [[bile]].
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1875|author=Felix von Niemeyer|translators=Geoorge H. Humphreys; Charles E. Hackley|title=A Text-book of Practical Medicine, with Particular Reference to Physiology and Pathological Anatomy|pageurl=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=h2cMAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA692&dq=%22acholia%22%7C%22acholias%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi3s4HMwpXPAhVGkZQKHb04DfsQ6AEIiwEwFg#v=onepage&q=%22acholia%22%7C%22acholias%22&f=false|page=692
|passage=The intensely bilious color of the liver shows that the discoloration of the contents of the intestines is not due to arrested production of bile, that is to '''acholia'''.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1884|title=The Journal of the American Medical Association|volume=2|pageurl=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=B_ZGAQAAMAAJ&q=%22acholia%22%7C%22acholias%22&dq=%22acholia%22%7C%22acholias%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi3s4HMwpXPAhVGkZQKHb04DfsQ6AEIWTAM|page=320
|passage=This then illustrates '''acholia''' in the literal sense of the word, and explains the absence of icterus in spite of the complete obliteration of the ductus communis choledochus.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2012|author=Carmen Gallego Herrera; Enrique Medina Benítez|chapter=Case 1: Percutaneous Ultrasound-guided Liver Biopsy|editors=María I. Martínez-León; Antonio Martínez-Valverde; Luisa Ceres-Ruiz|title=Imaging for Pediatricians: 100 Key Cases|pageurl=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=1JjprTfHstAC&pg=PA163&dq=%22acholia%22%7C%22acholias%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi3s4HMwpXPAhVGkZQKHb04DfsQ6AEIbzAR#v=onepage&q=%22acholia%22%7C%22acholias%22&f=false|page=163
|passage=A 1-month 3-week-old infant with a history of neonatal jaundice, cholestasis, and '''acholia''' is admitted to our hospital to rule out biliary atresia and further treatment.}}

